The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Chennai, July 4: Megasoft will acquire a 60 per cent stake in Beam AG, in an all-cash deal, the company said today. The German IT services company has a turnover of euro 1.4 million. Megasoft, however, did not disclose the deal size. The acquisition, which is subject to necessary statutory clearances, would give Megasoft a base in Europe, said G.V. Kumar, CEO and MD. A product-based technology company, Megasoft has operations in the US, UK, Singapore, Malaysia and Germany.

 Mumbai, July 4: The Reserve Bank of India has allowed single-branch banks and banks operating in a single district to classify non-performing assets based on 180-day delinquency norms instead of 90 days. This is expected to facilitate urban co-operative banks improve their performance.

 New Delhi, July 4: Air-India today announced new flights to Hong Kong, Seoul, Bangkok, Singapore and Kuala Lumpur from New Delhi starting July 7. 

 Mumbai, July 4: The Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) has decided to withdraw the suspension order on 20 scrips out of a total of 73, as the companies have submitted data on their shareholding pattern.

 Mumbai, July 4: The Securities Appellate Tribunal today admitted an appeal filed by UBS Securities Asia Ltd against the Securities and Exchange Board of India?s order that barred the company from issuing participatory notes for underlying Indian shares.

 New Delhi, July 4: Solaris Holdings Ltd has increased its stake in Crompton Greaves Ltd to 12.53 per cent, the company informed the National Stock Exchange.

 Calcutta, July 4: The tea plantation workers? unions today threatened to go for an indefinite strike at over 300 tea gardens in north Bengal following an inconclusive tripartite meeting with garden owners and the state government on their demand for wage revision.




